  m_Name: PokedexBird
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  entryId: bird_crow
  commonName: Crow
  scientificName: Corvus corone
  icon: {fileID: 2800000, guid: 8e5481a3ce647014c8df18fc9532d71b, type: 3}
  category: Bird
  habitat: Forest edges
  height: 0.45 m
  weight: 0.40 - 0.60 kg
  diet: Omnivore
  rarity: Common
  shortDescription: A clever woodland bird that watches from above and reacts quickly to movement.
  behaviorNotes: Crows travel in small groups and are often seen taking short flights between perches and open ground.
  observationTips: Look near tree lines and open clearings. They are easiest to spot when they pause to observe the player.
  funFact: Crows can remember faces and may return to watch places that interest them.
  facts:
  - Birds can be a good first discovery for the Pokedex.
  - The existing Living Birds demo already provides a strong wildlife base for the module.
  - Crows are highly observant and often respond to nearby disturbances.
